intervals provide a measure of uncertainty for predictions on regression problems. For example, a 95% prediction interval indicates that 95 out of 100 times, the true value will fall between the lower and upper values of the range. This is different from a simple point prediction that might represent the center of the uncertainty [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://machinelearningmastery.com/prediction-intervals-for-deep-learning-neural-networks/\">Prediction Intervals for Deep Learning Neural Networks</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://machinelearningmastery.com\">Machine Learning Mastery</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class=\"simplesocialbuttons simplesocial-simple-icons simplesocialbuttons_inline simplesocialbuttons-align-left post-12202 post  simplesocialbuttons-inline-no-animation\">\n<button class=\"ssb_tweet-icon\"  data-href=\"https://twitter.com/share?text=Prediction+Intervals+for+Deep+Learning+Neural+Networks&url=https://machinelearningmastery.com/prediction-intervals-for-deep-learning-neural-networks/\" rel=\"nofollow\" onclick=\"javascript:window.open(this.dataset.href, '', 'menubar=no,toolbar=no,resizable=yes,scrollbars=yes,height=600,width=600');return false;\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"icon\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 72 72\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h72v72H0z\"/><path class=\"icon\" fill=\"#fff\" d=\"M68.812 15.14c-2.348 1.04-4.87 1.744-7.52 2.06 2.704-1.62 4.78-4.186 5.757-7.243-2.53 1.5-5.33 2.592-8.314 3.176C56.35 10.59 52.948 9 49.182 9c-7.23 0-13.092 5.86-13.092 13.093 0 1.026.118 2.02.338 2.98C25.543 24.527 15.9 19.318 9.44 11.396c-1.125 1.936-1.77 4.184-1.77 6.58 0 4.543 2.312 8.552 5.824 10.9-2.146-.07-4.165-.658-5.93-1.64-.002.056-.002.11-.002.163 0 6.345 4.513 11.638 10.504 12.84-1.1.298-2.256.457-3.45.457-.845 0-1.666-.078-2.464-.23 1.667 5.2 6.5 8.985 12.23 9.09-4.482 3.51-10.13 5.605-16.26 5.605-1.055 0-2.09